It's not possible to edit site layout when the Easy Reader Theme has been selected. Confluence displays the message "You can not customise the site look and feel while a theme is active. You must first disable the currently configured theme."

However Easy Reader Theme relies on standard decorators. So it should be possible to edit them. Moreover if we customize the decorators while Default Theme is activated and then  switch back to Easy Reader, the changes are available in the Easy Reader Theme.

{panel:title=Atlassian Status as of 30/08/2010|borderStyle=solid|borderColor=#3C78B5| titleBGColor=#3C78B5| bgColor=#E7F4FA}
Several workarounds are available for users experiencing this problem.

* *Method 1* The user macro can be edited to include an extra {{<}}. So instead of {{<script...>}} one would use {{<<script...>}} The problem with this workaround is the macro will display an extra {{<}} if the user macro is used in a page. To work around that, you could create 2 versions of the macro. One with the extra {{<}} and one without.
* *Method 2* If desired, the theme .vmd files can be directly edited and the HTML can be placed in there. Note that this will affect all spaces that use the theme.
{panel}

If a user macro that renders HTML that contains a <script> tag is used in the left navigation of the documentation theme, the left angle bracket is stripped away, breaking the HTML and causing it to be treated as text by the browser.
For example a user macro with this HTML:
{code:html}
<script type="text/javascript">
alert('Hello World!');
</script>
{code}
Will render as:
{code:html}
script type="text/javascript">
alert('Hello World!');
</script>
{code}

